{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192373493,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_gQI59dpm0oJ1yUUHTXPv7359","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-03-signup.html"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-03-signup.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: <!DOCTYPE html>\n2: <html lang=\"en\">\n3: <head>\n4: <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n5: <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n6: <title>NestFind — Create Account</title>\n7: <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n8: <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n9: <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n10: <style>\n11: *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\n12: body{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n13: .root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n14: .navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n15: .nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n16: .nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n17: .nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n18: .nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n19: .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n20: .btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}\n21: .btn-primary:hover{box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(74,144,217,0.3);transform:translateY(-1px)}\n22: .btn-ghost{background:transparent;color:#F1F5F9;height:40px;padding:0 16px;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px}\n23: .btn-ghost:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n24: .btn-secondary{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);color:#F1F5F9;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);font-size:14px}\n25: .btn-secondary:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1)}\n26: .btn-danger{background:rgba(248,113,113,0.15);color:#F87171;height:40px;padding:0 16px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.2);font-size:13px}\n27: .btn-danger:hover{background:rgba(248,113,113,0.25)}\n28: .card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:24px}\n29: .card:hover{box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(74,144,217,0.15);background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n30: input[type=\"text\"],input[type=\"email\"],input[type=\"password\"],input[type=\"tel\"],textarea,select{height:48px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:10px;padding:0 16px;color:#F1F5F9;font-size:14px;font-family:inherit;outline:none;width:100%}\n31: input:focus,textarea:focus,select:focus{border-color:rgba(74,144,217,0.5);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(74,144,217,0.1)}\n32: input::placeholder,textarea::placeholder{color:#64748B}\n33: textarea{height:auto;padding:12px 16px;resize:vertical;min-height:100px}\n34: label{display:block;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:#94A3B8;margin-bottom:6px}\n35: .form-group{margin-bottom:16px}\n36: .form-link{color:#4A90D9;font-size:13px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500}\n37: .form-link:hover{color:#5BA0E9}\n38: .badge{display:inline-block;padding:2px 10px;border-radius:9999px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600}\n39: .badge-success{color:#4ADE80;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(74,222,128,0.3)}\n40: .badge-warning{color:#FBBF24;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(251,191,36,0.3)}\n41: .badge-error{color:#F87171;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(248,113,113,0.3)}\n42: .var-nav-bar{position:fixed;top:12px;right:12px;display:flex;gap:6px;background:rgba(8,11,20,0.9);backdrop-filter:blur(16px);padding:6px 10px;border-radius:10px;z-index:9999;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);font-size:11px;flex-wrap:wrap;max-width:95vw}\n43: .var-nav-bar a{color:#64748B;text-decoration:none;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:5px;transition:all 0.2s;white-space:nowrap}\n44: .var-nav-bar a.active{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff}\n45: .var-nav-bar a:hover:not(.active){color:#F1F5F9;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n46: .var-nav-bar .sep{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);font-size:10px}\n47: .error-text{color:#F87171;font-size:12px;margin-top:4px}\n48: .divider{height:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);margin:24px 0}\n49: .auth-wrapper{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:calc(100vh - 73px);padding:24px}\n50: .auth-card{width:100%;max-width:420px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:40px}\n51: .auth-card h2{font-size:28px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:-0.02em}\n52: .auth-card .subtitle{color:#94A3B8;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:32px;line-height:1.5}\n53: .form-row{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:16px}\n54: .form-check{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-size:13px;color:#94A3B8}\n55: .form-check input[type=\"checkbox\"]{width:16px;height:16px;accent-color:#4A90D9;cursor:pointer}\n56: .divider-text{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;color:#64748B;font-size:12px;margin:24px 0}\n57: .divider-text::before,.divider-text::after{content:'';flex:1;height:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n58: .auth-footer{text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#94A3B8;margin-top:24px}\n59: .auth-footer a{color:#4A90D9;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500}\n60: .auth-footer a:hover{color:#5BA0E9}\n61: .label-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px}\n62: .label-row label{margin-bottom:0}\n63: </style>\n64: </head>\n65: <body>\n66: <nav class=\"var-nav-bar\">\n67: <a href=\"A-01-landing.html\">Landing</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n68: <a href=\"A-02-login.html\">Login</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n69: <a href=\"A-03-signup.html\" class=\"active\">Signup</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n70: <a href=\"A-04-forgot-password.html\">Forgot</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n71: <a href=\"A-05-reset-password.html\">Reset</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n72: <a href=\"A-06-search.html\">Search</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n73: <a href=\"A-07-detail.html\">Detail</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n74: <a href=\"A-08-favorites.html\">Favs</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n75: <a href=\"A-09-inquiries.html\">Inq</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n76: <a href=\"A-10-profile.html\">Prof</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n77: <a href=\"A-11-admin-login.html\">AdLog</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n78: <a href=\"A-12-admin-dashboard.html\">AdDash</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n79: <a href=\"A-13-admin-properties.html\">AdProp</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n80: <a href=\"A-14-admin-property-form.html\">AdForm</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n81: <a href=\"A-15-admin-inquiries.html\">AdInq</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n82: <a href=\"A-16-admin-users.html\">AdUsr</a>\n83: </nav>\n84: <div class=\"root\">\n85: <nav class=\"navbar\">\n86:   <div class=\"nav-logo\">NestFind</div>\n87:   <div class=\"nav-links\">\n88:     <a href=\"A-06-search.html\">Browse</a>\n89:     <a href=\"A-01-landing.html\">Home</a>\n90:   </div>\n91: </nav>\n92: <div class=\"auth-wrapper\">\n93:   <div class=\"auth-card\">\n94:     <h2>Create your account</h2>\n95:     <p class=\"subtitle\">Join NestFind to save favorites and submit inquiries</p>\n96: \n97:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n98:       <label for=\"fullname\">Full Name</label>\n99:       <input type=\"text\" id=\"fullname\" placeholder=\"John Doe\">\n100:     </div>\n101: \n102:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n103:       <label for=\"email\">Email address</label>\n104:       <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" placeholder=\"you@example.com\">\n105:     </div>\n106: \n107:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n108:       <div class=\"label-row\">\n109:         <label for=\"phone\">Phone number</label>\n110:         <span class=\"badge badge-warning\">Optional</span>\n111:       </div>\n112:       <input type=\"tel\" id=\"phone\" placeholder=\"+1 (555) 000-0000\">\n113:     </div>\n114: \n115:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n116:       <label for=\"password\">Password</label>\n117:       <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" placeholder=\"Create a strong password\">\n118:     </div>\n119: \n120:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n121:       <label for=\"confirm-password\">Confirm Password</label>\n122:       <input type=\"password\" id=\"confirm-password\" placeholder=\"Re-enter your password\">\n123:     </div>\n124: \n125:     <div class=\"form-group\">\n126:       <label class=\"form-check\">\n127:         <input type=\"checkbox\">\n128:         I agree to the <a href=\"#\" class=\"form-link\" style=\"font-size:13px\">Terms of Service</a> and <a href=\"#\" class=\"form-link\" style=\"font-size:13px\">Privacy Policy</a>\n129:       </label>\n130:     </div>\n131: \n132:     <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" style=\"width:100%\">Create Account</button>\n133: \n134:     <div class=\"divider-text\">or</div>\n135: \n136:     <div class=\"auth-footer\">\n137:       Already have an account? <a href=\"A-02-login.html\">Sign in</a>\n138:     </div>\n139:   </div>\n140: </div>\n141: </div>\n142: </body>\n143: </html>\n\n(End of file - total 143 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n<title>NestFind — Create Account</title>\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n<style>\n*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\nbody{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n.root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n.navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n.nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n.nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n.nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n.nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n.btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n.btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-03-signup.html","time":{"start":1779192373189,"end":1779192373492}},"id":"prt_e402119ee001G4jW5yYLOswC8n","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","messageID":"msg_e40210196001Tin5h9ZwUt4z11"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192375097,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_pFklt4MWebp8vbMI6y8S5026","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Component Patterns\n2: \n3: Modern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n8: \n9: ### Why Function Components\n10: \n11: All components use function components with TypeScript for:\n12: \n13: - Explicit type safety for props\n14: - Consistent component signatures\n15: - Clear prop interface documentation\n16: - Better IDE autocomplete\n17: \n18: ### Basic Pattern\n19: \n20: ```typescript\n21: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n22: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n23: \n24: interface MyComponentProps {\n25:   /** User ID to display */\n26:   userId: number;\n27:   /** Optional callback when action occurs */\n28:   onAction?: () => void;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export default function MyComponent({ userId, onAction }: MyComponentProps) {\n32:   return (\n33:     <div className=\"p-4\">\n34:       User: {userId}\n35:       <Button onClick={onAction}>Action</Button>\n36:     </div>\n37:   );\n38: }\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Key Points:**\n42: \n43: - Props interface defined separately with JSDoc comments\n44: - Destructure props in parameters\n45: - Default export at bottom\n46: - Use Tailwind classes for styling\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Shadcn/UI Component Usage\n51: \n52: ### Available Components\n53: \n54: Shadcn/UI components are in `~/components/ui/`:\n55: \n56: ```typescript\n57: // Buttons\n58: import { Button, buttonVariants } from '~/components/ui/button';\n59: \n60: // Forms\n61: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n62: import { Label } from '~/components/ui/label';\n63: import {\n64:   Form,\n65:   FormControl,\n66:   FormField,\n67:   FormItem,\n68:   FormLabel,\n69:   FormMessage,\n70: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n71: \n72: // Cards\n73: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Button Component\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n80: \n81: // Variants\n82: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n83: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n84: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Delete</Button>\n85: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n86: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n87: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n88: \n89: // Sizes\n90: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n91: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n92: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n93: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n94: \n95: // States\n96: <Button disabled>Disabled</Button>\n97: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width</Button>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Card Component\n101: \n102: ```typescript\n103: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n104: \n105: <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n106:   <CardHeader>\n107:     <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>\n108:   </CardHeader>\n109:   <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n110:     <p>Card content goes here</p>\n111:   </CardContent>\n112: </Card>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Form Components (MANDATORY PATTERN — all forms must use this)\n116: \n117: ```typescript\n118: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n119: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n120: import { z } from 'zod';\n121: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n122: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n123: import {\n124:   Form,\n125:   FormControl,\n126:   FormField,\n127:   FormItem,\n128:   FormLabel,\n129:   FormMessage,\n130: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n131: \n132: const schema = z.object({\n133:   email: z.string().email(),\n134:   password: z.string().min(6),\n135: });\n136: \n137: type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n138: \n139: export default function LoginForm() {\n140:   const form = useForm<FormData>({\n141:     resolver: zodResolver(schema),\n142:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n143:   });\n144: \n145:   return (\n146:     <Form {...form}>\n147:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n148:         <FormField\n149:           control={form.control}\n150:           name=\"email\"\n151:           render={({ field }) => (\n152:             <FormItem>\n153:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n154:               <FormControl>\n155:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter email\" {...field} />\n156:               </FormControl>\n157:               <FormMessage />\n158:             </FormItem>\n159:           )}\n160:         />\n161:         <Button type=\"submit\">Submit</Button>\n162:       </form>\n163:     </Form>\n164:   );\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## CVA (Class Variance Authority)\n171: \n172: ### What is CVA\n173: \n174: CVA is used for component variants in Shadcn/UI. It creates type-safe variant props.\n175: \n176: ### Example from Button Component\n177: \n178: ```typescript\n179: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n180: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n181: \n182: const buttonVariants = cva(\n183:   // Base styles applied to all buttons\n184:   'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all',\n185:   {\n186:     variants: {\n187:       variant: {\n188:         default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',\n189:         destructive: 'bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90',\n190:         outline: 'border bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n191:         secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',\n192:         ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n193:         link: 'text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline',\n194:       },\n195:       size: {\n196:         default: 'h-9 px-4 py-2',\n197:         sm: 'h-8 px-3',\n198:         lg: 'h-10 px-6',\n199:         icon: 'size-9',\n200:       },\n201:     },\n202:     defaultVariants: {\n203:       variant: 'default',\n204:       size: 'default',\n205:     },\n206:   }\n207: );\n208: \n209: // Usage in component\n210: function Button({\n211:   className,\n212:   variant,\n213:   size,\n214:   ...props\n215: }: React.ComponentProps<'button'> & VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>) {\n216:   return (\n217:     <button\n218:       className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}\n219:       {...props}\n220:     />\n221:   );\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## When to Add a Variant vs Use className (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: All reusable components must follow these rules:\n230: \n231: 1. **Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop** — this allows call-site-specific layout overrides\n232: 2. **Add a cva variant when:**\n233:    - The style combination appears at 2+ call sites\n234:    - It represents a semantic state (error, success, warning, loading, ghost, compact)\n235:    - It changes the visual identity of the component (not just layout)\n236: 3. **Use `className` when:**\n237:    - The override is context-specific and used at only 1 call site\n238:    - It's a layout concern (width, height, padding offset, positioning)\n239:    - It's a dynamic value passed from props (e.g., `className={style.text}`)\n240: \n241: ```typescript\n242: // ✅ CORRECT — Semantic state as variant\n243: <Input variant=\"error\" />\n244: \n245: // ✅ CORRECT — One-off layout as className\n246: <Input className=\"pl-10\" />\n247: \n248: // ❌ WRONG — Duplicated error classes at call sites\n249: <Input className=\"border-red-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-red-500/20\" />\n250: \n251: // ❌ WRONG — Creating a new component for a style difference\n252: // Instead, add a variant to the existing component\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## cn() Utility for Class Merging\n258: \n259: ### What is cn()\n260: \n261: `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional class merging:\n262: \n263: ```typescript\n264: // ~/lib/utils.ts\n265: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n266: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n267: \n268: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n269:   return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n270: }\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Usage Examples\n274: \n275: ```typescript\n276: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n277: \n278: // Conditional classes\n279: <div className={cn(\n280:   'p-4 bg-background',\n281:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n282:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n283: )} />\n284: \n285: // Merging with overrides\n286: <Button className={cn(\n287:   buttonVariants({ variant: 'default' }),\n288:   'w-full' // Override width\n289: )} />\n290: \n291: // Array of conditions\n292: <div className={cn([\n293:   'base-class',\n294:   condition1 && 'class-1',\n295:   condition2 && 'class-2',\n296: ])} />\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## asChild Pattern (Radix UI)\n302: \n303: ### What is asChild\n304: \n305: The `asChild` prop allows composing components with custom elements:\n306: \n307: ```typescript\n308: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n309: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n310: \n311: // Button as Link\n312: <Button asChild>\n313:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n314: </Button>\n315: \n316: // Button as anchor\n317: <Button asChild variant=\"link\">\n318:   <a href=\"https://example.com\">External Link</a>\n319: </Button>\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### How it Works\n323: \n324: The Button uses Radix's `Slot` component:\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';\n328: \n329: function Button({ asChild = false, ...props }) {\n330:   const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';\n331:   return <Comp {...props} />;\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### IMPORTANT: asChild + Link Anti-Pattern\n336: \n337: **NEVER use `asChild` with `Link` inside `DropdownMenuItem`:**\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: // ❌ CAUSES VISUAL \"BLINK\" ON FIRST RENDER\n341: <DropdownMenuItem asChild>\n342:   <Link to={`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`}>\n343:     <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n344:     View Details\n345:   </Link>\n346: </DropdownMenuItem>\n347: \n348: // ✅ USE onClick with navigate() INSTEAD\n349: <DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => navigate(`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`)}>\n350:   <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n351:   View Details\n352: </DropdownMenuItem>\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Better: Use the ActionMenu Component**\n356: \n357: For table action menus, use the reusable `ActionMenu` component:\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { ActionMenu } from '~/components/ui/action-menu';\n361: \n362: <ActionMenu\n363:   items={[\n364:     {\n365:       label: 'View Details',\n366:       icon: <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n367:       href: `/dashboard/users/${user.id}`,  // Uses navigate() internally\n368:     },\n369:     {\n370:       label: 'Delete',\n371:       icon: <Trash2 className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n372:       onClick: () => handleDelete(user.id),\n373:       variant: 'destructive',\n374:     },\n375:   ]}\n376: />\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Component Structure Template\n382: \n383: ### Recommended Order\n384: \n385: ```typescript\n386: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from 'react';\n387: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n388: \n389: // Redux\n390: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n391: \n392: // UI Components\n393: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n394: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '~/components/ui/card';\n395: \n396: // Utilities\n397: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n398: \n399: // Types\n400: import type { User } from '~/types/user';\n401: \n402: // 1. PROPS INTERFACE (with JSDoc)\n403: interface MyComponentProps {\n404:   /** The ID of the entity to display */\n405:   entityId: number;\n406:   /** Optional callback when action completes */\n407:   onComplete?: () => void;\n408:   /** Display mode */\n409:   mode?: 'view' | 'edit';\n410: }\n411: \n412: // 2. COMPONENT DEFINITION\n413: export default function MyComponent({\n414:   entityId,\n415:   onComplete,\n416:   mode = 'view',\n417: }: MyComponentProps) {\n418:   // 3. HOOKS (in this order)\n419:   // - Redux hooks\n420:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n421:   const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.currentUser);\n422:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n423: \n424:   // - Local state\n425:   const [selectedItem, setSelectedItem] = useState<string | null>(null);\n426:   const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(mode === 'edit');\n427: \n428:   // - Memoized values\n429:   const filteredData = useMemo(() => {\n430:     return data.filter((item) => item.active);\n431:   }, [data]);\n432: \n433:   // - Effects\n434:   useEffect(() => {\n435:     // Setup\n436:     return () => {\n437:       // Cleanup\n438:     };\n439:   }, []);\n440: \n441:   // 4. EVENT HANDLERS (with useCallback for passed handlers)\n442:   const handleItemSelect = useCallback((itemId: string) => {\n443:     setSelectedItem(itemId);\n444:   }, []);\n445: \n446:   const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {\n447:     try {\n448:       // Save logic\n449:       onComplete?.();\n450:     } catch (error) {\n451:       console.error('Failed to save:', error);\n452:     }\n453:   }, [onComplete]);\n454: \n455:   // 5. RENDER\n456:   return (\n457:     <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n458:       <CardHeader>\n459:         <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold\">My Component</h2>\n460:       </CardHeader>\n461:       <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n462:         <p className={cn('text-muted-foreground', loading && 'opacity-50')}>\n463:           {user?.email}\n464:         </p>\n465:         <Button onClick={handleSave} disabled={loading}>\n466:           {loading ? 'Loading...' : 'Save'}\n467:         </Button>\n468:       </CardContent>\n469:     </Card>\n470:   );\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Component Separation\n477: \n478: ### When to Split Components\n479: \n480: **Split into multiple components when:**\n481: \n482: - Component exceeds 200 lines\n483: - Multiple distinct responsibilities\n484: - Reusable sections\n485: - Complex nested JSX\n486: \n487: **Example:**\n488: \n489: ```typescript\n490: // ❌ AVOID - Monolithic\n491: function MassivePage() {\n492:   // 500+ lines\n493:   // Header logic\n494:   // Form logic\n495:   // Table logic\n496:   // Modal logic\n497: }\n498: \n499: // ✅ PREFERRED - Modular\n500: function Page() {\n501:   return (\n502:     <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n503:       <PageHeader />\n504:       <SearchForm onSearch={handleSearch} />\n505:       <DataTable data={filteredData} />\n506:       <ActionModal open={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} />\n507:     </div>\n508:   );\n509: }\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ### When to Keep Together\n513: \n514: **Keep in same file when:**\n515: \n516: - Component < 100 lines\n517: - Tightly coupled logic\n518: - Not reusable elsewhere\n519: - Simple presentation component\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Lazy Loading Pattern\n524: \n525: ### When to Lazy Load\n526: \n527: Lazy load components that are:\n528: \n529: - Heavy (DataGrid, charts, rich text editors)\n530: - Route-level components\n531: - Modal/dialog content (not shown initially)\n532: - Below-the-fold content\n533: \n534: ### How to Lazy Load\n535: \n536: ```typescript\n537: import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n538: \n539: // Lazy load heavy component\n540: const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./HeavyEditor'));\n541: \n542: // Usage with Suspense\n543: function Page() {\n544:   return (\n545:     <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>\n546:       <HeavyEditor />\n547:     </Suspense>\n548:   );\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Component Communication\n555: \n556: ### Props Down, Events Up\n557: \n558: ```typescript\n559: // Parent\n560: function Parent() {\n561:   const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n562: \n563:   return (\n564:     <Child\n565:       data={data} // Props down\n566:       onSelect={setSelectedId} // Events up\n567:     />\n568:   );\n569: }\n570: \n571: // Child\n572: interface ChildProps {\n573:   data: Data[];\n574:   onSelect: (id: string) => void;\n575: }\n576: \n577: export default function Child({ data, onSelect }: ChildProps) {\n578:   return (\n579:     <ul>\n580:       {data.map((item) => (\n581:         <li key={item.id} onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}>\n582:           {item.name}\n583:         </li>\n584:       ))}\n585:     </ul>\n586:   );\n587: }\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ### Using Redux for Shared State\n591: \n592: ```typescript\n593: // When state needs to be shared across components\n594: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n595: import { selectItem } from '~/redux/features/itemSlice';\n596: \n597: function Child() {\n598:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n599:   const selectedId = useAppSelector((state) => state.item.selectedId);\n600: \n601:   const handleSelect = (id: string) => {\n602:     dispatch(selectItem(id));\n603:   };\n604: \n605:   return <div onClick={() => handleSelect('123')}>Select</div>;\n606: }\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Summary\n612: \n613: **Modern Component Recipe:**\n614: \n615: 1. Function components with TypeScript props interface\n616: 2. Shadcn/UI components from `~/components/ui/`\n617: 3. `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n618: 4. Tailwind CSS for styling\n619: 5. `useAppSelector` and `useAppDispatch` for Redux\n620: 6. Event handlers with `useCallback` when passed to children\n621: 7. Default export at bottom\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## MANDATORY: Async State Handling\n626: \n627: Every component that fetches data MUST handle all three states:\n628: \n629: ```typescript\n630: // MANDATORY: Loading state\n631: if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;\n632: \n633: // MANDATORY: Error state\n634: if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;\n635: \n636: // MANDATORY: Empty state (distinct from error)\n637: if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState title=\"No items found\" />;\n638: \n639: // Happy path\n640: return <DataList items={data} />;\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Rules:**\n644: - Loading skeleton (not spinner) for initial data loads\n645: - Error state with retry button for API failures\n646: - Empty state for zero results (NOT the same component as error)\n647: - Error boundaries wrapping route-level components for uncaught errors\n648: \n649: ## MANDATORY: No Business Logic in Components\n650: \n651: Components must only handle rendering and event delegation:\n652: \n653: ```typescript\n654: // BAD: Business logic in component\n655: const filteredUsers = users.filter(u => u.role === 'admin' && u.isActive);\n656: const sortedUsers = filteredUsers.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n657: \n658: // GOOD: Logic in selector/utility\n659: const activeAdmins = useAppSelector(selectActiveAdmins);\n660: ```\n661: \n662: **See Also:**\n663: \n664: - [styling-guide.md](styling-guide.md) - Tailwind CSS patterns\n665: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Form patterns\n666: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Component Patterns\n\nModern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n\n### Why Function Components\n\nAll components use function components with TypeScript for:\n\n- Explicit type safety for props\n- Consistent component signatures\n- Clear prop interface documentation\n- Better IDE autocomplete\n\n### Basic Pattern\n\n```typescript","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779192374795,"end":1779192375096}},"id":"prt_e40212127001xePNsWsyRZ8B7R","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","messageID":"msg_e40210196001Tin5h9ZwUt4z11"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192376649,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_voiPpVCgjWIBSprCfCCy5897","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/best-practices.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/best-practices.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Frontend Best Practices\n2: \n3: ## React Component Best Practices\n4: \n5: ### Component File Organization\n6: \n7: ```typescript\n8: // GOOD: Component with typed props, hooks at top\n9: interface ButtonProps {\n10:     variant?: 'primary' | 'outline';\n11:     children: React.ReactNode;\n12:     onClick?: () => void;\n13:     disabled?: boolean;\n14: }\n15: \n16: export function Button({ variant = 'primary', children, onClick, disabled }: ButtonProps) {\n17:     const { t } = useTranslation();\n18:     const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);\n19: \n20:     const handleClick = () => {\n21:         if (onClick) onClick();\n22:     };\n23: \n24:     return (\n25:         <button\n26:             className={cn(\n27:                 'px-4 py-2 rounded-md',\n28:                 variant === 'primary' && 'bg-blue-500 text-white',\n29:                 variant === 'outline' && 'border border-gray-300',\n30:                 disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n31:             )}\n32:             onClick={handleClick}\n33:             disabled={disabled || isLoading}\n34:         >\n35:             {children}\n36:         </button>\n37:     );\n38: }\n39: \n40: // BAD: Untyped props, inline styles, logic in JSX\n41: export function Button(props) {\n42:     return (\n43:         <button style={{ padding: '10px' }} onClick={() => props.onClick && props.onClick()}>\n44:             {props.children}\n45:         </button>\n46:     );\n47: }\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Component Organization Pattern\n51: \n52: ```\n53: components/\n54: ├── ui/          # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)\n55: ├── atoms/       # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n56: ├── modals/      # Modal/dialog overlays (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n57: ├── shared/      # Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)\n58: ├── layouts/     # Layout wrappers\n59: └── guards/      # Route guards\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Component Categorization Decision Tree\n63: \n64: Before creating a component, answer:\n65: 1. Is it a Shadcn primitive? → `ui/` (lowercase file name)\n66: 2. Is it a modal or dialog overlay? → `modals/` (PascalCase, `Modal` suffix)\n67: 3. Is it small, reusable, and decoupled from any specific page or layout? → `atoms/`\n68: 4. Is it tightly coupled to a specific layout section (nav, sidebar, breadcrumb)? → `shared/`\n69: 5. Is it a page layout wrapper? → `layouts/`\n70: 6. Is it a route access gate? → `guards/`\n71: \n72: ### Inline Component Rule\n73: Never define reusable sub-components as local named functions at the bottom of a page file.\n74: - If it has its own props interface → extract to the correct folder\n75: - If it uses `forwardRef` → extract to `atoms/` or `modals/`\n76: - If it contains its own `useState` or `useEffect` → strong signal to extract\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## State Management Patterns\n81: \n82: ### When to Use Each State Type\n83: \n84: | State Type | Use Case | Example |\n85: |------------|----------|---------|\n86: | **Local State** (`useState`) | UI-only state, form inputs, mutation loading | Modal open/close, input values, submitting flag |\n87: | **Redux** (READ thunks) | All server state + global app state | User list, projects, tasks, auth, app settings |\n88: | **Redux** (sync reducers) | Auth state, optimistic updates | loginSuccess, logout, markOneRead |\n89: | **URL State** | Shareable/bookmarkable state | Filters, pagination, search |\n90: \n91: > **Do NOT use TanStack Query.** All data fetching uses Redux async thunks (`createAsyncThunk` in service files). Mutations use direct service calls with local `useState` for loading.\n92: \n93: ### Redux Toolkit Slice Pattern\n94: \n95: ```typescript\n96: // GOOD: Typed slice with initial state\n97: import { createSlice, PayloadAction } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';\n98: import type { AuthState, AuthUser } from '@/types/redux/auth';\n99: \n100: const initialState: AuthState = {\n101:     user: null,\n102:     isAuthenticated: false,\n103:     isLoading: false,\n104:     error: null,\n105: };\n106: \n107: export const authSlice = createSlice({\n108:     name: 'auth',\n109:     initialState,\n110:     reducers: {\n111:         loginStart: (state) => {\n112:             state.isLoading = true;\n113:             state.error = null;\n114:         },\n115:         loginSuccess: (state, action: PayloadAction<AuthUser>) => {\n116:             state.user = action.payload;\n117:             state.isAuthenticated = true;\n118:             state.isLoading = false;\n119:         },\n120:         loginFailure: (state, action: PayloadAction<string>) => {\n121:             state.isLoading = false;\n122:             state.error = action.payload;\n123:         },\n124:         logout: (state) => {\n125:             state.user = null;\n126:             state.isAuthenticated = false;\n127:         },\n128:     },\n129: });\n130: \n131: export const { loginStart, loginSuccess, loginFailure, logout } = authSlice.actions;\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### React Query Key Factory Pattern\n135: \n136: ```typescript\n137: // GOOD: Centralized query key factory\n138: export const authKeys = {\n139:     all: ['auth'] as const,\n140:     user: () => [...authKeys.all, 'user'] as const,\n141:     session: () => [...authKeys.all, 'session'] as const,\n142: };\n143: \n144: export const userKeys = {\n145:     all: ['users'] as const,\n146:     lists: () => [...userKeys.all, 'list'] as const,\n147:     list: (filters: UserFilters) => [...userKeys.lists(), filters] as const,\n148:     details: () => [...userKeys.all, 'detail'] as const,\n149:     detail: (id: string) => [...userKeys.details(), id] as const,\n150: };\n151: \n152: // Usage in hooks\n153: export function useUser(id: string) {\n154:     return useQuery({\n155:         queryKey: userKeys.detail(id),\n156:         queryFn: () => userService.getById(id),\n157:     });\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### React Query with Mutations\n162: \n163: ```typescript\n164: // GOOD: Mutation with cache invalidation\n165: export function useLogin() {\n166:     const queryClient = useQueryClient();\n167:     const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n168: \n169:     return useMutation({\n170:         mutationFn: (data: LoginRequest) => authService.login(data),\n171:         onSuccess: (response) => {\n172:             dispatch(loginSuccess(response.data.user));\n173:             queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: authKeys.all });\n174:         },\n175:         onError: (error) => {\n176:             dispatch(loginFailure(error.message));\n177:         },\n178:     });\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Form Handling — MANDATORY: React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form\n185: \n186: > **ALL forms MUST use this pattern. Manual `useState` for form fields is FORBIDDEN.**\n187: \n188: ### Zod Schema Definition\n189: \n190: ```typescript\n191: // GOOD: Schema with custom error messages\n192: import { z } from 'zod';\n193: \n194: export const loginSchema = z.object({\n195:     username: z.string().min(1, 'Username is required'),\n196:     password: z.string().min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters'),\n197:     rememberMe: z.boolean().optional(),\n198: });\n199: \n200: export type LoginFormData = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>;\n201: \n202: // Schema with cross-field validation\n203: export const registerSchema = z\n204:     .object({\n205:         username: z.string().min(3, 'Username must be at least 3 characters'),\n206:         email: z.string().email('Invalid email address').optional(),\n207:         password: z.string().min(8, 'Password must be at least 8 characters'),\n208:         confirmPassword: z.string(),\n209:     })\n210:     .refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {\n211:         message: 'Passwords do not match',\n212:         path: ['confirmPassword'],\n213:     });\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### Form Component Pattern (MANDATORY)\n217: \n218: ```typescript\n219: // GOOD: Form with React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form components\n220: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n221: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n222: import { loginSchema, type LoginFormData } from '~/utils/validations/auth';\n223: import { Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage } from '~/components/ui/form';\n224: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n225: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n226: \n227: export function LoginForm() {\n228:     const form = useForm<LoginFormData>({\n229:         resolver: zodResolver(loginSchema),\n230:         defaultValues: { username: '', password: '' },\n231:     });\n232: \n233:     const onSubmit = (data: LoginFormData) => { /* ... */ };\n234: \n235:     return (\n236:         <Form {...form}>\n237:             <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>\n238:                 <FormField control={form.control} name=\"username\" render={({ field }) => (\n239:                     <FormItem>\n240:                         <FormLabel>Username</FormLabel>\n241:                         <FormControl><Input placeholder=\"Username\" {...field} /></FormControl>\n242:                         <FormMessage />\n243:                     </FormItem>\n244:                 )} />\n245:                 <FormField control={form.control} name=\"password\" render={({ field }) => (\n246:                     <FormItem>\n247:                         <FormLabel>Password</FormLabel>\n248:                         <FormControl><Input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Password\" {...field} /></FormControl>\n249:                         <FormMessage />\n250:                     </FormItem>\n251:                 )} />\n252:                 <Button type=\"submit\">Login</Button>\n253:             </form>\n254:         </Form>\n255:     );\n256: }\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI Patterns\n262: \n263: ### Class Composition with cn()\n264: \n265: ```typescript\n266: // lib/utils.ts\n267: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n268: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n269: \n270: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n271:     return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n272: }\n273: \n274: // Usage\n275: <div className={cn(\n276:     'flex items-center gap-2',\n277:     isActive && 'bg-blue-100',\n278:     disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n279: )} />\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ### Component Variants with cva\n283: \n284: ```typescript\n285: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n286: \n287: const buttonVariants = cva(\n288:     'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors',\n289:     {\n290:         variants: {\n291:             variant: {\n292:                 primary: 'bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary/90',\n293:                 outline: 'border border-input bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n294:                 ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n295:             },\n296:             size: {\n297:                 sm: 'h-8 px-3 text-sm',\n298:                 md: 'h-10 px-4',\n299:                 lg: 'h-12 px-6 text-lg',\n300:             },\n301:         },\n302:         defaultVariants: {\n303:             variant: 'primary',\n304:             size: 'md',\n305:         },\n306:     }\n307: );\n308: \n309: interface ButtonProps extends VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {\n310:     children: React.ReactNode;\n311: }\n312: \n313: export function Button({ variant, size, children }: ButtonProps) {\n314:     return <button className={buttonVariants({ variant, size })}>{children}</button>;\n315: }\n316: ```\n317: \n318: > **Variant-First Rule (MANDATORY):** All reusable components MUST use cva variants for visual differences that appear across call sites. The `className` prop is for call-site-local overrides only (width, height, spacing, positioning). Never copy-paste a group of Tailwind classes across multiple call sites — extract it as a variant. Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop.\n319: \n320: ### Responsive Design\n321: \n322: ```typescript\n323: // Mobile-first responsive pattern\n324: <div className=\"\n325:     grid grid-cols-1          /* Mobile: 1 column */\n326:     sm:grid-cols-2            /* Tablet: 2 columns */\n327:     lg:grid-cols-3            /* Desktop: 3 columns */\n328:     gap-4\n329: \">\n330:     {items.map(item => <Card key={item.id} {...item} />)}\n331: </div>\n332: \n333: // Hide/show based on screen size\n334: <nav className=\"hidden md:flex\">Desktop nav</nav>\n335: <nav className=\"flex md:hidden\">Mobile nav</nav>\n336: ```\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## Socket.IO Frontend Patterns\n341: \n342: ### Frontend Socket Service Pattern\n343: \n344: ```typescript\n345: // GOOD: Singleton service with typed events\n346: class ChatSocketService {\n347:     private socket: Socket | null = null;\n348: \n349:     connect(): Socket {\n350:         if (this.socket?.connected) return this.socket;\n351: \n352:         this.socket = io('/chat', {\n353:             withCredentials: true,  // Send cookies\n354:             transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],\n355:             reconnection: true,\n356:             reconnectionAttempts: 5,\n357:         });\n358: \n359:         return this.socket;\n360:     }\n361: \n362:     onNewMessage(callback: (event: NewMessageEvent) => void): void {\n363:         this.socket?.on('message:new', callback);\n364:     }\n365: \n366:     offNewMessage(): void {\n367:         this.socket?.off('message:new');\n368:     }\n369: }\n370: \n371: export const chatSocketService = new ChatSocketService();\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### React Hook Pattern for Socket Rooms\n375: \n376: ```typescript\n377: // GOOD: Hook with proper cleanup and React Query integration\n378: export function useChatRoomSocket({ roomId, enabled = true }) {\n379:     const queryClient = useQueryClient();\n380: \n381:     useEffect(() => {\n382:         if (!enabled || !chatSocketService.isConnected()) return;\n383: \n384:         chatSocketService.joinRoom(roomId);\n385: \n386:         const handleNewMessage = (event: NewMessageEvent) => {\n387:             if (event.roomId !== roomId) return;\n388: \n389:             // Update React Query cache directly for instant UI update\n390:             queryClient.setQueryData<ChatMessage[]>(\n391:                 chatKeys.messages(roomId),\n392:                 (old = []) => [...old, event.message]\n393:             );\n394:         };\n395: \n396:         chatSocketService.onNewMessage(handleNewMessage);\n397: \n398:         return () => {\n399:             chatSocketService.offNewMessage();\n400:             chatSocketService.leaveRoom(roomId);\n401:         };\n402:     }, [roomId, enabled, queryClient]);\n403: }\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## Related Guides\n409: \n410: For more detailed patterns, see:\n411: - [Component Patterns](component-patterns.md) - Detailed component structure\n412: - [Data Fetching](data-fetching.md) - API integration patterns\n413: - [TanStack Query](tanstack-query.md) - Query patterns\n414: - [TypeScript Standards](typescript-standards.md) - Type safety guidelines\n415: - [Authentication Architecture](authentication-architecture.md) - Auth flow details\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## Playwright E2E Testing\n420: \n421: ### Page Object Model Pattern\n422: \n423: ```typescript\n424: // test/page-objects/login.page.ts\n425: import { Locator, Page } from '@playwright/test';\n426: \n427: export class LoginPage {\n428:     readonly page: Page;\n429:     readonly usernameInput: Locator;\n430:     readonly passwordInput: Locator;\n431:     readonly submitButton: Locator;\n432:     readonly errorMessage: Locator;\n433: \n434:     constructor(page: Page) {\n435:         this.page = page;\n436:         this.usernameInput = page.getByTestId('username-input');\n437:         this.passwordInput = page.getByTestId('password-input');\n438:         this.submitButton = page.getByRole('button', { name: /login/i });\n439:         this.errorMessage = page.getByRole('alert');\n440:     }\n441: \n442:     async goto() {\n443:         await this.page.goto('/auth/login');\n444:     }\n445: \n446:     async login(username: string, password: string) {\n447:         await this.usernameInput.fill(username);\n448:         await this.passwordInput.fill(password);\n449:         await this.submitButton.click();\n450:     }\n451: \n452:     async expectErrorMessage(message: string) {\n453:         await expect(this.errorMessage).toContainText(message);\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: ### Custom Test Fixtures\n459: \n460: ```typescript\n461: // test/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts\n462: import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';\n463: import { LoginPage } from '../page-objects/login.page';\n464: \n465: type AuthFixtures = {\n466:     loginPage: LoginPage;\n467:     login: (username: string, password: string) => Promise<void>;\n468: };\n469: \n470: export const test = base.extend<AuthFixtures>({\n471:     loginPage: async ({ page }, use) => {\n472:         const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);\n473:         await use(loginPage);\n474:     },\n475:     login: async ({ page }, use) => {\n476:         const loginFn = async (username: string, password: string) => {\n477:             const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);\n478:             await loginPage.goto();\n479:             await loginPage.login(username, password);\n480:             await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');\n481:         };\n482:         await use(loginFn);\n483:     },\n484: });\n485: \n486: export { expect } from '@playwright/test';\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ### Test Structure\n490: \n491: ```typescript\n492: // test/tests/auth/login.spec.ts\n493: import { test, expect } from '../../fixtures/auth.fixture';\n494: \n495: test.describe('Login Page', () => {\n496:     test.beforeEach(async ({ loginPage }) => {\n497:         await loginPage.goto();\n498:     });\n499: \n500:     test('should display login form', async ({ loginPage }) => {\n501:         await expect(loginPage.usernameInput).toBeVisible();\n502:         await expect(loginPage.passwordInput).toBeVisible();\n503:         await expect(loginPage.submitButton).toBeVisible();\n504:     });\n505: \n506:     test('should show error for invalid credentials', async ({ loginPage }) => {\n507:         await loginPage.login('invalid', 'wrong');\n508:         await loginPage.expectErrorMessage('Invalid credentials');\n509:     });\n510: \n511:     test('should redirect to dashboard on success', async ({ page, login }) => {\n512:         await login('admin@example.com', 'Password123!');\n513:         await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');\n514:     });\n515: });\n516: ```\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## MANDATORY Rules (from Base Architecture)\n521: \n522: ### Utility Function Rules\n523: \n524: - **Arrow function syntax only**: `export const fn = (...): ReturnType => { ... }` — NEVER `function` declarations\n525: - **Location**: All utility functions MUST live in `app/utils/` organized by domain:\n526:   - `utils/formatting.ts` — Date/time, number, string formatting\n527:   - `utils/badges.ts` — CSS class mapping for badges, status indicators\n528:   - `utils/avatar.ts` — Avatar color generation, initials extraction\n529:   - `utils/pagination.ts` — Page number calculation, pagination helpers\n530:   - `utils/csv.ts` — CSV export/download utilities\n531:   - `utils/dates.ts` — Date arithmetic, trend calculations\n532: - **Never inline**: Helper functions that are NOT React components or hooks MUST NOT be defined inside page/component files\n533: - **Named exports only**: Use `export const`, never `export default` for utility functions\n534: - **Deduplication**: If utility is needed in multiple files, extract to `utils/` — never copy-paste\n535: \n536: ### Service & Slice Pattern\n537: \n538: - `createAsyncThunk` MUST NOT appear in slice files (`redux/features/*Slice.ts`)\n539: - All thunks live in service files (`services/httpServices/*Service.ts`)\n540: - Slice files only contain: thunk imports, initial state, sync reducers, `extraReducers`\n541: - Consumer pages/components import thunks from service files, not slice files\n542: \n543: ### Type Organization\n544: \n545: - ALL interfaces and types defined in `types/*.d.ts` — NONE inline in components, pages, hooks, or utils\n546: - Component `*Props` interfaces in domain type file or `types/components.d.ts`\n547: - Types imported with `import type` syntax\n548: - No duplicate type names across files\n549: \n550: ### Code Quality Mandates\n551: \n552: - **No `any` type** — use specific types or `unknown` with type guards\n553: - **No `console.log`** in production code — use proper logger\n554: - **No hardcoded mock data** arrays in production components\n555: - **No placeholder data** (John Doe, lorem ipsum, test@example.com)\n556: - **No commented-out code** — delete it, git has history\n557: - **Components < 300 lines** (excluding imports/exports) — split if larger\n558: - **Nesting depth < 5 levels** — extract sub-components if deeper\n559: - **httpService wrapper required** — no raw axios/fetch calls in components or slices\n560: - **No direct API calls** in components or Redux slices — always go through service layer\n561: \n562: ### Import Order\n563: \n564: 1. React / React Router\n565: 2. External libraries (Redux, Zod, etc.)\n566: 3. Internal aliases (`~/components`, `~/services`, etc.)\n567: 4. Relative imports\n568: 5. Type imports (with `import type`)\n569: 6. Styles\n\n(End of file - total 569 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Frontend Best Practices\n\n## React Component Best Practices\n\n### Component File Organization\n\n```typescript\n// GOOD: Component with typed props, hooks at top\ninterface ButtonProps {\n    variant?: 'primary' | 'outline';\n    children: React.ReactNode;\n    onClick?: () => void;\n    disabled?: boolean;\n}\n\nexport function Button({ variant = 'primary', children, onClick, disabled }: ButtonProps) {\n    const { t } = useTranslation();\n    const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);\n\n    const handleClick = () => {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/best-practices.md","time":{"start":1779192376347,"end":1779192376648}},"id":"prt_e40212736001ikR3M3nhNeCKRI","sessionID":"ses_1bfdf023affeT00JeJZg7buQNd","messageID":"msg_e40210196001Tin5h9ZwUt4z11"}}
